#napaunity day 7: solidarity âœŠğŸ¾ sigma strives to be progressive and encourages our members to stand in solidarity with the suvivors, the disenfranchised, the minority voices, etc. .
ğŸ“ lawrence, ks | our members of the alpha mu charter had the opportunity to meet, introduce, and listen to tamara burke, the founder of the #metoo movement at a talk on the ku campus. .
ğŸ“ washington, dc | sigmas at gw university wear black to stand in solidarity against workplace sexual assualt and harassment.
.
ğŸ“ albany, ny | our alpha chapter and sigrho at ualbany collaborate on a workshop to "break the silence" on domestic/sexual violence as a part of dvam.
.
ğŸ“ charlottesville, va | some sigmas at uva participate in a campus campaign on fighting the notion of apida americans being a model minority in the us.

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - iâ€™ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now iâ€™m about to go back, knowing what i know, and weâ€™re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trumpâ€™s election, trumpeted the return of their â€œpopulist heroâ€ on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publicationâ€™s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if thereâ€™s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: iâ€™m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents â€“ on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - iâ€™ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now iâ€™m about to go back, knowing what i know, and weâ€™re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trumpâ€™s election, trumpeted the return of their â€œpopulist heroâ€ on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publicationâ€™s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if thereâ€™s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: iâ€™m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents â€“ on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - iâ€™ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now iâ€™m about to go back, knowing what i know, and weâ€™re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trumpâ€™s election, trumpeted the return of their â€œpopulist heroâ€ on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publicationâ€™s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if thereâ€™s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: iâ€™m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents â€“ on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

text:
2018
what an intense year. 
from losing 30kgâ€™s, losing my grandmother who is and was my everything. to surviving some of the most challenging things that has crossed my path. some i have been very vocal about, some not so much. from losing chances for love, to making wrong decisions. i am proud to say, 2018 has not broken me. and nothing will. every challenge that came my way, i had the option of throwing in the rope like previously. but i am better, stronger and more confident than ever. i want to take this opportunity to thank every single friend and family member for always being there. thank you. 
i can only try and motivate the next person, with experiences iâ€™ve had over the years and the most important life hack iâ€™ve learnt this year - everything in life is a choice. some might not agree, some might. being ugly - is a choice - being weak - is a choice. being poor, is a choice! being unhappy in a recurring situation- is a choice! 
choose to focus on yourself in 2019, set your goals. choose to be happy. choose you. 
donâ€™t ever give up.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if thereâ€™s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: iâ€™m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents â€“ on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - iâ€™ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now iâ€™m about to go back, knowing what i know, and weâ€™re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trumpâ€™s election, trumpeted the return of their â€œpopulist heroâ€ on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publicationâ€™s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if thereâ€™s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: iâ€™m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents â€“ on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - iâ€™ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now iâ€™m about to go back, knowing what i know, and weâ€™re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trumpâ€™s election, trumpeted the return of their â€œpopulist heroâ€ on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publicationâ€™s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if thereâ€™s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: iâ€™m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents â€“ on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
fight like a girl || slapping someone with weak wrists.âŒ
_______________________________________________________________________
fight like a girl || to never give up, never back down. to stay optimistic in the face of adversity. be true to yourself, even when those around you may doubt what you're doing. sometimes the ones we love can, unintentionally, project their own fears onto others in hopes of protecting them. follow your intuition, it's a very powerful ally. and if you don't have keen intuition then get into the practice of quieting down your mind so you can listen. fighting like a girl means you don't let your circumstance define you. you defy it, you empower yourself, you use the circumstance as an opportunity for growth and not as a casting call to play the role of victim. this doesn't mean you go completely numb. there are going to be days when you need to cry, you need to break things, scream, eat that bowl (eh hem, not pint) of ice-cream, call that friend or relative and tell them how miserable you are that things have changed in your life so drastically.

text:
this morning i committed a mortal sin apparently. in an honest mistake i credited a photo to the wrong person, for which i received a sarcastic, childish reply for. when i realised my mistake i immediately corrected it, and gave the photographer a bit of his own medicine back. i've had a number of dms supporting me for standing up to him as they could clearly see i had made an honest mistake and did the right thing as soon as i knew. anyone who is a regular 'reader' of my posts knows that, i always where possible, credit a person's work. 
sadly this particular precious little petal seems to have a bit of an issue with his eq, because after immediately doing what he asked of me ie crediting him for the photo he still went on. unfortunately for him, numerous people seen it and weren't impressed with his attitude so he's lost potential clientele through his own actions. they will no doubt tell a few more......etc etc etc.

i forgive him. he obviously needs to do some work on his ego, get down off that pedastal he's put himself on and pull his head out of his arse: because here's a  newsflash - the sun doesn't revolve around him and nor does ig. that's exactly how he came across today to numerous people and i ended up receiving more followers from it. not because i did anything wonderful. i simply stood up to a male who thought he could bully me. that doesn't work in this day and age. it especially doesn't go down well since the #metoo movement began.

if i ever make a mistake in crediting the wrong person for a piece of work, a polite dm to me will have the situation resolved as soon as i see it, but don't for one minute think that you're going to suddenly appear on my page with bullying and sarcastic comments, and get away with your rubbish. i don't like conflict at all but i give as good as i get.

finally please let me say how thankful i am for my authentic genuine contacts/followers. thankfully my 'tribe' doesn't consist of any precious or precocious little petals and they have talent and intestinal fortitude and then some. thank you for your words of support today. it's all good. karma's a bitch.

text:
to all the writers like me
i see you
walking away from
pain all day
only to return to it's lap
as dawn transcends into dusk.

i see you
finding comfort in darkness
the same kind you found in
dad's arms once,
while the entire world 
scorns
at your eccentricity.

i see you
direly trying to hide
your poems from ma
in the fear of seeing her 
crash to the ground
with dilemma ridden eyes
seeing her burn those sheets
like it was your pyre

i see you
endlessly lying about
why you write
confusing passion with ache
when it is the only thing
keeping you alive.

i see you
i see your heart break
into two
as you soak words
with blood
and sponge the yellow walls
of your room
you don'tÂ  know
when you fell in love
with spilling blood
instead of it flowing through your veins.

i see you
every night
as you pick up the quill
and wonder
why do you relate to plath more
when wordsworth 
was the one
who wrote happier poems.
you eat black for breakfast 
and bukowski's melancholy for lunch
while emptiness fills your stomach
before you sleep.

i see you
not sleep
but write that
emptiness away
so that you wake up
looking full the next day
so that the world
doesn't question
the void in your eyes
and that lack of light.

i see you
and i know 
you see me
so can we just spend
one evening 
aching together 
not smiling or laughing.
one evening where 
we are not faced with the
brunt of explaining 
this overwhelming numbness.
one evening where we
analyse why our poems don't rhyme anymore
as darkness lulls us to sleep.
till that one evening,
i will continue seeing you
from the corner
quietly.
.
.
arunima sengupta.
(@adding_soul_to_words)
.
.

@the.asian.feminist is now on @medium! in our first blog, we look back at several events in 2018: how women survivors in asia are failed by their countriesâ€™ legal system. we write:
â€˜dictionary merriam-webster has chosen â€œjusticeâ€ as the word of the year 2018, saying it was the websiteâ€™s top lookup of the year. with this news, we should reflect on how justice has materialized for women in asia, especially those who experience gender-based violence. the answer is unfortunately not encouraging. recent court cases, from malaysia to indonesia, from hong kong to china, highlight that the legal system not only fails to protect but also is very hostile and punitive toward women survivors.â€™ we look at baiq nuril maknunâ€™s case in indonesia, a #dv survivor who was denied divorce in china, an abused mother who was punished for raising domestic violence in hong kongâ€™s family court and others. 
special thanks to @monaeltahawy whose reference to judith herman and her powerful quote is very useful to this essay, and prof #katemanne who coined the term â€œhimpathyâ€. dedicated to all women survivors out there. link in bio. 
#vaw #gbv #metoo #dv #domesticviolence #sexualharassment #sexualassault

text:
dr. christine blasey ford was at one point of the year the most talked about woman in the world. she bravely gave up her anonymity to publicly accuse brett kavanaugh of sexual assault. in response to her statement of her ordeal she has been the publicly mocked and ridiculed (including by president trump himself) as well as the assault itself deemed by some as too trivial. her personal and familyâ€™s security was also at risk by death threats with them having to move house. with all of this kavanaugh was narrowly voted onto and sworn onto the supreme court - the highest court in the federal judiciary of the united states. 
dr. blasey fordâ€™s public statement has had a lastly impact, not perhaps on kavanaugh, but on everyone who has ever been the victim of sexual assault. she has given those a voice, the bravery to speak up, and has brought the conversation of consent to the forefront. 
thank you dr. blasey ford for your calmness and courage in the face of all you have faced.

#shero #hero #equalrights #drblaseyford #feminist #metoo #speakup #fff

text_retweet:
reposted from @beyond_thoughtss -  to all the writers like me
i see you
walking away from
pain all day
only to return to it's lap
as dawn transcends into dusk.

i see you
finding comfort in darkness
the same kind you found in
dad's arms once,
while the entire world 
scorns
at your eccentricity.

i see you
direly trying to hide
your poems from ma
in the fear of seeing her 
crash to the ground
with dilemma ridden eyes
seeing her burn those sheets
like it was your pyre

i see you
endlessly lying about
why you write
confusing passion with ache
when it is the only thing
keeping you alive.

i see you
i see your heart break
into two
as you soak words
with blood
and sponge the yellow walls
of your room
you don'tÂ  know
when you fell in love
with spilling blood
instead of it flowing through your veins.

i see you
every night
as you pick up the quill
and wonder
why do you relate to plath more
when wordsworth 
was the one
who wrote happier poems.
you eat black for breakfast 
and bukowski's melancholy for lunch
while emptiness fills your stomach
before you sleep.

i see you
not sleep
but write that
emptiness away
so that you wake up
looking full the next day
so that the world
doesn't question
the void in your eyes
and that lack of light.

i see you
and i know 
you see me
so can we just spend
one evening 
aching together 
not smiling or laughing.
one evening where 
we are not faced with the
brunt of explaining 
this overwhelming numbness.
one evening where we
analyse why our poems don't rhyme anymore
as darkness lulls us to sleep.
till that one evening,
i will continue seeing you
from the corner
quietly.
.
.
arunima sengupta.
(@adding_soul_to_words)
.
.

text:
with the new year upon us, 
we take some time to look back through some of our highlights of 2018 with gratitude, optimism and humility. we are so grateful 
to have had such a beautiful 2018 and we owe it to our muses, supporters, partners, employees and all of you, who believe in us. 
we begin our memories of 2018 with the watershed golden globes, an award carpet and ceremony marked by the collective strength of so many women who joined together to use fashion as a protest, a visual language against the injustices faced as survivors of, and in support of the survivors of the #metoo movement. we are proud to have dressed two musesâ€”  golden globe nominee @issarae in atelier prabal gurung and @kerrywashington in a special look straight from our newest collection. both looks were auctioned off to benefit @timesupnow in support for this moment of resistance, resilience and unity.
#pgworld #pgmuse #beautywithsubstance #femininitywithabite #modernglamour #luxurywithsoul

text:
day 1: management mantra 2018@scwbgn

with the blessings of the almighty, day 1 of management mantra witnessed events like *let's talk (a ted talk show)* where the students *talked about gender equality, self motivation, traveling* etc.
*symposium* witnessed a heated *discussion about #metoo* whereas *business plan competition* put forth various products and services that would make our life a better one.
last but not the least, the *students of science department have exhibited 12 under the model-making competition*.
the honourable judges felt extremely delighted to see such marvels and have already provided *an opportunity to exhibit the same at institute of science, bhu*.

text:
"the best thing a woman can bring to relationship to make her valuable in the eyes of a man who truly wants her is not her ability to help him financially or her ability to be able to take care of herself." this woman is the female derrick jaxn telling lies to women. let's just analyze the first sentence.

a man does not value  a woman that can take care of herself.......false.

most men deal with women who cant take care of themselves financially. if taking care of yourself financially is the primary form of taking care of yourself, you are lost, whether you are a man or a woman.

taking care of yourself includes taking care of your mind, body and spirit. a feminine healthy minded woman is a woman that takes care of herself mebtally and that is rare and attractive. a woman who lives by a higher spiritual code is a woman that takes care of herself spiritually and nothing in a woman is sexier than that.

a woman that comes to the table looking to build will be more desireable than a woman seeking handouts needing a man to take care of her. the average woman in the west is seeing handouts, you have 100,000+ women that have begged men for cashapp and paypal money in the last 25 minutes alone.

proverbs 31:14-22

this woman works and provides for her family. she shops for material to create clothes so her husband doesn't have to spend money on clothes. she saves him money with her hands and brings in money with her hands.

14 she is like the merchant ships,  bringing her food from afar.
15 she gets up while it is still night;  she provides food for her family  and portions for her female servants.
16 she considers a field and buys it;  out of her earnings she plants a vineyard.
17 she sets about her work vigorously;  her arms are strong for her tasks.
18 she sees that her trading is profitable,  and her lamp does not go out at night.
19 in her hand she holds the distaff  and grasps the spindle with her fingers.
20 she opens her arms to the poor  and extends her hands to the needy.
21 when it snows, she has no fear for her household;  for all of them are clothed in scarlet.
22 she makes coverings for her bed;  she is clothed in fine linen and purple.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and

text:
some days i loathe the feeling of her neediness, breastfeeding a toddler is demanding on your body and mind. feeding aversions are real, being touched out is real and feeling resentful of her constant need for my body is real too.

there have been huge personal boundary lessons come up in my experience of breastfeeding. throughout the unpacking and healing of my history of sexual abuse i came to realize that my personal boundaries were totally fucked up from a childhood where my body was not my own. my body was merely a plaything for my abusers and as a result i have never exercised my own bodily autonomy very well.

breastfeeding a toddler has taught me to exercise my â€œfuck no muscleâ€ (thanks for the term @the_angela_gallo) more than i have ever had the power to in my life, and itâ€™s definitely not always easy, but for helping me find this i am forever grateful to her.

as we approach my personal goal of 2 years i will continue to honour my own new sense of autonomy and boundaries and the feelings of discomfort and sit with them.

breastfeeding is a two-way relationship, and we will stop, when i am done or she is done. whichever comes first.

i used to be that woman. i made my entire world revolve around the man i was involved with at the time.  it would not be an exaggeration to say that all of the men i ever dated were terrible matches for me. i couldnâ€™t give them what they wanted and they certainly couldnâ€™t give me what i wanted or needed.  i was raised by incredibly strong, resilient women. yet they didnâ€™t know the horrors i suffered and as a result, i became an expert at hiding that pain. i walked a very dark path full of anguish and secret sorrow for many years.  eventually, i destroyed myself. healing was not easy-it was filled with pain and hard work that will continue for the rest of my life. as i laid alone in the rubble that was once my life, tears steaming down my face,  i heard the voices and felt the spirit of all the strong women in my family who had passed before, imploring me, â€œget up!! get up, get up, get up! this is your truth. own it.  you are stronger than you think. you will survive this. you will heal...and you will rise.â€ #shewillrise #abusesurvivor #womanwarrior #selflove #selfworth #strengthquotes #powerfulwomen #yougotthis #yougogirl #womanempowerment #youhavesuchaprettyface #gotfaith #survivor #metoo #courage #courageouswomen  #becourageous #trustgod

text: how about a day after christmas present? ladies and gentlemen...i'd like to introduce you to our 2019 sctc keynote speaker, the incomparable van barnes! in terms of googleability, van is probably best known as the first person to out the cis male lead actor who was eventually fired from amazonâ€™s award winning and critically acclaimed tv show transparent when she joined theÂ #metooÂ movement, disclosing her experience working several seasons as personal assistant to the lead actor. although her first on-screen credit came in francis ford coppolaâ€™s 1983 movie "rumble fish", she can be found on youtube in the 1995 wigstock movie as well as a string of 1990â€™s daytime talk show appearances, and was a nyc club kid in the early 90â€™s. she was also featured in two seasons of "i am cait" on the e channel. she transitioned twice before she got it right and today is living her dream married to big daddy living a hetero-normative hillbilly lifestyle keeping chickens in the ozark foothills of missouri and does hair in nearby st. louis. her green acres trans-life is inspirational to many as she offers her brutally honest satirical opinions about her journey. we are so happy to have her with us for our 2019 conference! she's awesome!!! #sctc2019 #greatertogether #vanbarnes

text:
this post is for a friend. everyone's been jumping on the #metoo movement this year. i've kind of kept quiet, because i am very open about the fact that i was sexually assaulted and have been for most my 20s. it's not something to hide in shame over, because i didn't do anything wrong. sometimes i joke about it now, because it diffuses the memory and gives it less power. 
but my friend and i were talking about the kavanagh case. and dude, if i wanted to prove someone raped me when i was 13, i would have no proof. there is literally no proof against kavanagh...or against my rapist. that doesn't mean my rape didn't happen, or that christine ford is a liar. we don't know because there's not enough proof. but what this shows me is to keep talking. because i pray the world my nieces and nephews grow up in will be one where when something happens, you tell someone immediately and the rapist gets in trouble because there's fucking proof. no more shame or hidden family secrets. and men, your voice is in listening, really, hearing what we are saying. because if you do, you'll see us. 
#metoomovement #feminism #rapeculture #jointheclub #slutwalk #circa2014 #maleprivilege #girlpower

text:
do you feel like no one gets how unsafe it feels to open up emotionally or physically, even to your partner? this is a common feeling for anyone who has been on the receiving end of sexual abuse. we currently have 2 spots available in our sexual abuse support group for women in their 20s-30s. our clinicians are ready to help you process and move beyond those painful feelings that keep you feeling just out of reach from your loved ones. call us for questions or to register. link to contact in bio.

#sexualabuse #sexualabusesurvivor #metoo #sexualheath #trauma #ptsd #relationshipgoals

do you feel like no one gets how unsafe it feels to open up emotionally or physically, even to your partner? this is a common feeling for anyone who has been on the receiving end of sexual abuse. we currently have 2 spots available in our sexual abuse support group for women in their 20s-30s. our clinicians are ready to help you process and move beyond those painful feelings that keep you feeling just out of reach from your loved ones. call us for questions or to register. link to contact in bio.

#sexualabuse #sexualabusesurvivor #metoo #sexualheath #trauma #ptsd #relationshipgoals

â €

the remaining details are not significant to my story, but something was taken from me that night that iâ€™ll never get back.
â €

what i...deserved???

text:
the omen days of christmas have begun!  this celtic tradition helps you find themes to empower each month of the coming year.  starting today, dec 26, each of the next 12 days represents a month of the year, 2019,  so today applies to january. look for something that seems to have meaning for you, and that is your january theme. over the 12 days, you do this for each month. 
traditionally, these omens were found in nature, perhaps by taking a walk to identify something that has significance for you, and noting that this is a message for that month.  in my personal practice, i donâ€™t limit the omen search to nature, but choose something that speaks to me that day.  often it is in my family or personal life, or even from something sparked by a fb post.  this morning, for example, i am attracted to a video retrospective on the building of womenâ€™s inner fire for change in 2018, starting with the #metoo movement.  i may use this as my january omen, and stay alert to ideas for personal action during the month. 
last year was my first year doing this, and i loved the process.  i wrote a few words about each month in 2018, and referred to them throughout the year, especially on the first day of the month. it was fun to see these as themes and build an action intention around them.  there is no wrong way to do this, so whatever works for you is fine.  what i like most about the omen days is that the meaning comes entirely from what seems important to me. last year, my intentions were about my personal life, but this year i think i am going to expand my themes to include some culture changing goals. i am doing this again, starting today.  who else is doing it with me?  feel free to tag me in posts, post in this thread, or post over on my karen crane, lifestyle alchemy page.  letâ€™s have some fun!  #wisdomwork  #lifestylealchemy
name: Karen Crane

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:

what if the sweet almost indulgent feel of doing something solely for you was a universal nod in the direction you should do?

when i had a strict meal plan i used the energy of cravings to do something: yoga, dance, writing, hiking. 
when i was getting sober i used the energy of cravings and irritation to notice things around me i had ignored for years. 
maybe, the flutter that we may call nerves or anxiety is really just energy saying, â€œyesâ€

fill your own cup first so we can teach all generations howâ€™s itâ€™s done.  because when one woman heals, she also heals her mother, her daughter and all the women around her. 
so.  much.  love.

text:
it's the festive season and it's supposed to  be a happy season for all, but my mood went dark immediately i saw this.
.
according to reports, she was 300 level university student and showed no signs or depression prior.
.
she took a poison to end her life but not before living a note, bidding her loved ones farewell.
.
depression is *not* a myth. it is real. it kills it's victim slowly, constantly pushing limits. .
please if you suspect depression in you or someone you know, report and seek help as soon as possible. you will be saving a life. .
if you do not know how to get help directly, send us a message on here and we'll walk the walk with you; but the first step is always breaking silence.
. 
you are not alone!!!
.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. heâ€™s the only straight man iâ€™ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

.
i was asked a lot about the big â€œtâ€ word this week: trust! .
.i heard again and again- can i recover confidence in myself making good life decisions? can i trust people again and stop feeling guilty after having said #metoo? or when i am smiling on the outside but aching on the inside..
.yes, you can with 1 simple tool, that we go more deeply into in my masterclass. bottom line inventory.
..here are simple steps to create yours:.
.take out a sheet of paper right now and write down all the things that you cannot stand. the things that piss you off. ğŸ“ give yourself 5 minutes to just go to townâ€¦ ..now trust, without judgement or letting that negative self talk creep on inâ€¦ write down 2 words next to each one. write down- 1) handle it. 2) cannot handle it..
.take a moment and be with your list. now send trust to that list. trust that you can and deserve to honor your bottom line. and see what it feels like to be with the handle it vs. not handle it side. ..see you in the next post! i hope you can have your list by then! .
.

text:
#suhelseth gets married to model girlfriend, #lakshmimenon, amidst sexual harassment rumours.

reports about #suhel #seth getting engaged to his model girlfriend, #lakshmi #menon, started doing the rounds right when he was accused of #sexual #harassment by multiple women from the industry. the two reportedly got engaged at his apartment in #gurugram and headed to #goa and #switzerland for a romantic post-engagement #vacation. the two have now tied the knot in a private ceremony at his apartment in gurugram, as per reports in #mumbai mirror. the two got married yesterday and a source told the daily, â€œit was a quiet, genteel affair, and the guests were people who are close to suhel and who he counts as friends.â€ the guests included #prafulpatel, #jaypanda, #amarsingh, #muzaffarali, #tasneem, tarun tejpal, #sheiladixit and a couple of other close friends. well, looks like congratulations are in order for the writer-columnist despite all the #sexualharassment accusations against him. the two havenâ€™t confirmed it on social #media yet or to any other portal, for that matter. while we are eagerly hoping to see an official announcement soon, we wish the #newlyweds #hearty #congratulations for their new life ahead. this has definitely come as a shock to many that the two are now married.

#metoo #metoomovement #aaiwa #news

text: my cover of when under ether by pj harvey. because. a lot of reasons. ethereal sounding. perplexing. suggestive of abortion. but not necessarily about that. suggestive of being under the influence of something, perhaps out of your control. suggestive of human kindness. i come to singing to story tell and this song has a purpose. for me it reminds me of when i was drugged (and assaulted) and the way that state can confuse you into thinking, in the immediate aftermath, everything is ok. everyone is nice. text:
i had a weird epiphany today. it was something like, in order to feel safe in the general area i have to believe they werenâ€™t all bad.

maybe only like, 78% bad or 82% bad. i thought about 63% bad for a while but that seemed too big a lie to sell to myself. i have them up as about 3500% bad at present so weâ€™re already talking quite a large reduction.

i should qualify â€œbadâ€. bad is a lot of things, like it turns out a feeling thatâ€™s â€œbadâ€ is a lot of different feelings. so â€œbadâ€ in this case is short for all of the forces of self-interest, lack of awareness, abuse of power, rigid thinking, absence of empathy, hypocrisy, privilege and so on.

it turns out â€œbadâ€ in this case is pretty broad so iâ€™m abbreviating it to bad.

then thereâ€™s parameters on â€œthemâ€ and they are utterly exclusive of anyone directly involved. itâ€™s a more collective, ultimately faceless entity, this â€œthemâ€. it has faces though of course, i could guess at some of them. i have guessed at some of them, but this guess work serves no value because i had to deal with a faceless them ultimately and it was not equivalent to the sum of its individual parts.

i have to believe that there was a point where further harm could have been caused but a decision was made not to. i have been attributing this to a lack of realisation on their part but maybe not.

it came to me after my inbox on twitter was once again full of stories from other autistic people in various types of litigation.

they all have their own collective faceless entities on the other side, and when there are opportunities to prolong or increase the harm done in a situation those faceless entities take these.

for the sake of the people who reached out to me i canâ€™t list the examples.

it changes perspective, when i look at my faceless them and consider what it could have done.

thatâ€™s not any kind of pass mind you, the bar is literally on the floor after all. just because someone like me came along and forced them to shove a small wedge underneath it doesnâ€™t mean weâ€™re done here, progress achieved, next issue please.

i think iâ€™ll settle on 82% bad, handing out acknowledgment for what should be a minimum standard is still a bit off.

i have to learn to let go, which is hard. 
you were all i knew. 
all i dreamt of.
all i wanted. 
i just didnâ€™t get that in return. 
you hurt me. 
i cried.

itâ€™s time to let go. 
i need to let go. 
i will let go. -carolynn m

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
this afternoon i took some time out for myself, allowed myself to be fully present and grounded. i am always drawn to water this is where i feel most at peace. watching the water cascade over the waterfall is so calming. self care is extremely important , more so when you are going through some challenging times, there is nothing selfish about it. i am so very blessed and grateful to be surrounded by some amazing people that walk alongside me, it is important to keep your tribe close, and let them help when you need it (still learning to do this) one step, one breath, one day at a time, thats all you can do.

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking â€˜ugh. totally uglyâ€™ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think itâ€™s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people donâ€™t necessarily know itâ€™s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so itâ€™s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that youâ€™re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of peopleâ€™s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldnâ€™t have seen, and couldnâ€™t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, â€œwould work for anyoneâ€. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean theyâ€™re mercenaries. theyâ€™ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

itâ€™s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing â€“ at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public â€“ our intimate family connections, our â€œlikesâ€, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole thatâ€™s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

itâ€™s time to change that mindset, and the start of the new year can be a good spot to start over.

text:
between stimulus and response there is a space. in that space is our power to choose our response. in our response lies our growth and our freedom. ~viktor e. frankl
. . . . .

my thoughts @viptravelgirl

iâ€™ve been thinking about this â€œspaceâ€ that viktor e. frankl refers to a lot these past few weeks. mostly because we seem to be in what i like to call a â€œsocial (re)awakeningâ€ on some many fronts; which has sparked new and also reignited old conversations on so many critical topics like the #metoo movement, #lgbt rights, #civialrights  and so much more.  i only mention these as examples because they are conversations fueled by passionate thoughts and options from many varied perspectives which further validate the meaning of this quote. iâ€™ve always valued my ability to acknowledge this space and use it to see beyond just myself. but i have discovered that this space can and has become somewhat of a burden iâ€™ve come to bare. why? because growing up as a bi-racial girl in conservative americaâ€¦iâ€™ve always felt obligated to work within the confines of this space. having control over my thoughts, feelings and actions were the best ways to navigate the narrow straights of society. but as iâ€™ve been working through a very emotionally challenging yearâ€¦iâ€™ve discovered that this space has become nothing more then a catch-allâ€¦a space for packaging up all the bullshit perspectives, ignorant ideologies and small-minded thoughts that iâ€™ve been forced to maneuver around over the years. rather then my â€œspaceâ€ being a place of growth and freedomâ€¦itâ€™s resembled something more closely to a glass box.

the takeaway:
while i will always seek first to understand and then to be understood. itâ€™s time for me to shatter my own glass ceiling in order to make room for myself.  itâ€™s time for me to get comfortable with letting others be uncomfortable. itâ€™s not my job to make me or my awesomeness more palpable for others to swallow. because at the end of the dayâ€¦if we are all honor our own spaces, weâ€™ll all be better off for it.

text: thrilled and proud to share this @ms_magazine article that #kohinurkhyumtithila wrote on @thewitchhuntshow. we are creating a space for diverse women to be heard and to heal - and to laugh along the way. i have been honored to witness so many brave witches sharing their truths and their talents over this past year. many thanks to @cszla for giving us a residency to develop the show and to all the funny, talented and courageous women (and a couple gents as well!) who have shared the stage. it has been an honor. special shout out to #gloriaiseli for helping bring this show to the next level and to ally wizard and good man human @michaeljsielaff who made the call that got the ball rolling and has been a supportive ally and diligent social media maven from the get go. and a witchinâ€™ big thank you to everyone who has come and put your tushies in the seats - we so appreciate your support as we have been discovering this show. excited for whatâ€™s to come, witches!! #witchplease #witchcrushwednesday #funnywomen #feminist #diverse #diversestories #theatreoftheabsurd #witchhunt #metoo #timesup #believeher #comedy #varietyshow #lathtr #witch #witchin #jointhecoven

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
christopher wylie, who worked with a cambridge university academic to obtain the data, told the observer: â€œwe exploited facebook to harvest millions of peopleâ€™s profiles. and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.â€ documents seen by the observer, and confirmed by a facebook statement, show that by late 2015 the company had found out that information had been harvested on an unprecedented scale. however, at the time it failed to alert users and took only limited steps to recover and secure the private information of more than 50 million individuals.

the data was collected through an app called thisisyourdigitallife, built by academic aleksandr kogan, separately from his work at cambridge university. through his company global science research (gsr), in collaboration with cambridge analytica, hundreds of thousands of users were paid to take a personality test and agreed to have their data collected for academic use.

however, the app also collected the information of the test-takersâ€™ facebook friends, leading to the accumulation of a data pool tens of millions-strong. facebookâ€™s â€œplatform policyâ€ allowed only collection of friendsâ€™ data to improve user experience in the app and barred it being sold on or used for advertising. the discovery of the unprecedented data harvesting, and the use to which it was put, raises urgent new questions about facebookâ€™s role in targeting voters in the us presidential election. it comes only weeks after indictments of 13 russians by the special counsel robert mueller which stated they had used the platform to perpetrate â€œinformation warfareâ€ against the us.

carole cadwalladr & emma graham-harrison
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
imelda cortez, a 20-year-old woman in el salvador, who was jailed with attempted murder after she gave birth to her rapistâ€™s baby in a toilet has been freed. cortez was rushed to the hospital in april 2017 after she gave birth to a baby girl fathered by her stepfather, who has raped and sexually abused her since she was 12, in the toilet. cortez said she did not know she was pregnant, but the doctor at the hospital suspected she had tried to abort the baby and called the authorities. cortez was then arrested and handed a 20 year jail sentence after prosecutors argued that failing to tell anyone about her pregnancy or seek medical attention for the baby amounted to attempted murder under the countryâ€™s laws, which completely ban abortions. however, on monday, a court ruled that cortez had not tried to kill her child and that she was free to go home. the judge concluded that the court could not have expected her to act differently given the emotional and psychological damage inflicted by the sexual violence she had suffered since childhood. cortez was greeted by family members and supporters outside the courtroom. (ğŸ“·: getty, reuters)

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
i don't think that i can articulate my why better than this! @evancarmichael is absolutely 110% on point!..................................... "i think the why in what you do comes from pain. and i think people are good people in general. like i think humans are good and i'm on team human.
and when you have gone through something painful, you just naturally want to make it easier for the other people who are suffering that same thing.
and i think that human nature is to try and avoid the pain and forget the pain, put it behind us. never go back there, it's a terrible place.
when i think if you actually want to help people you need to run back into your pain. understand what that meant to you and how bad it was and then whatever you did to get over it, then helping other people. make the road a little bit easier"

text:
i've seen this tweet circulate around a lot of feminist pages on here. apparently if two people's lives aren't ruined by a crime, the crime isn't a problem. gun violence isn't a problem because at least 2 people have been shot and lived through it. rape isn't a problem because at least 2 people have led successful lives after being raped. obviously the feminists who use this logic don't apply it universally to all similar situations, just the ones where it benefits the feminist narrative. it's such a laughable and stupid claim to make that false accusations aren't harmful because two people's lives weren't ruined (even though their lives and reputation were definitely damaged), not to mention completely dismissive and ignorant of the men who have had their lives ruined due to false accusations. people have lost jobs and school places over false accusations. people have even lost their lives to them but apparently those people's lives weren't ruined because that didn't happen to these two cherry picked men.

text:
to the ones who picked me before i was ripe enough;
the universe bears witness of all injustice,
witness in the form of the air that carries the secrets and cries i'd utter when i'd feel alone on nights filled with darkness of the past,
in the form of the fire that'd rage in my head and heart when i'd think of what life could've been otherwise,
in the form of tears that cleansed my face while i'd attempt to cleanse my body, as if water would wash off marks of your touch,
and in the form of the ground that i'd kneel to and prostrate, until i'd feel pure again,
the universe bears witness and the universe awaits.
#universe #black #tears #head #heart #fire #water #ground #air #ripe #metoo #body #pure #marks #darkness #timesup #secrets #cries #cleanse #rage #poetry #poem

i rewrote this for the women who have been through the storm and rain about beauty. vanity has swept through and told us that we should conform to a falsfied man's image that would never be satisfied. truth be told many women seek approval from those who are not complete themselves because of their own insecurities. i desire to be with a husband who can appreciate beauty not just from the outside, but can build on the inside by uplifting her as a priceless treasure. on my own walk with god, i asked if this was possible because of all the calamities and abuses that i suffer from counterfeits attracted to manipulation and control. i discovered that this is possible living bicariously through other couple's lives who weathered scrutiny, lust, and financial devastation. what is the storm you are willing to endure to protect your own relationship in god's eyesight? i know what i'm graced for and not graced for with boundaries and limitations in which others say, whoaaa! i listen to the politically and poetically correct individuals who spew vomit because will it work in my situation?? only heaven knows.......i will tell my issues to god who created me and can handle the burdens that i can share with everyone. #metoo 
i'm beautiful even with the scars and my hair nappy looking because it's my style that my culture can accept and heritage. look at my brown skin, its rich with education and intellectual sense that i follow and my mind is unrentlenting in grasping and then demonstrating with the manifestation of greatness and wealthy for your company as well as my family. @flowing

text:
//
forget fear first 
then show failure 
the way out /

don't run from your 
sadness, it'll stay anyways /
don't you know - 
everything you run from, 
chases you at a 
greater pace /

broken bones, 
broken homes, 
they're all screaming my 
name , i know /

but i can't return for 
ahead is the only 
direction i now know /
i know it hurts to hurt, 
when everyone is trying to 
save you /
but the hurt is a river 
without a mouth, 
his do you push it back? 
tell me about your losses, 
i'll tell you about my 
victories /
tell me you lost your moon, 
i'll tell you i went out 
looking for the sun /
look you miseries in the eye, 
tell them you're coming back
to take everything you 
left behind / to take back a heart 
that forgot its way home. 
don't run from the hurt, 
it is here only 
to have its share of your heart.
.
.

text_retweet:
repost @realkombucha 
such a great quote, it's so so so true. it's awful for a recovering alcoholic that is open and honest about the dangers of alcohol. people think it's acceptable to tell me that i should go to a meeting and generally rude to me when i choose wellness even when i tell them i went to rehab. it's so crazy how alcohol dominates everything 
the first work conferences i attended sober i was still shy about it and there was no water or non alcoholic drinks available so now i am much more vocal about how unacceptable it is to have no other option. for me this actually worked out well and i was happy to have non alcoholic drinks available at the last event!
at the end of my life i will not remember the years i wasted trying to drink away my problems and anxiety. instead i will be thankful for the rest of my life i learned how to thrive in life without numbing myself so other people are comfortable. when i see alcohol now i see pain and suffering, not the glamorous false lies that are sold to us

text: one of my favorite reads this month (and all of 2018) was â€œbraveâ€ by rose mcgowan. in this book rose talks about how she went from being born into a cult and how she ended up in another cult, hollywood. she talks about surviving a world where victims, specifically women, are molded to be victims by a patriarchal world. she talks about her experiences and holds nothing back. this book moved me completely. i have never felt so seen and heard and understood and that kind of connection is worth shouting about. 100% recommend for anyone who has been a victim of the world they live in, anyone who wants to understand how women feel and are treated, and anyone who loves rose mcgowanâ€™s work and activism as much as i do. i cannot stop thinking about it. absolute favorite memoir ever. â“who is an author you connected to? ğŸ¥€ #brave #rosearmy #rosemcgowan #metoo #bookreccomendation #memoir #books #activism

text:
//this poem is written in the point of view of a victim and is not personal to the writer//
my take on the #metoo movement. 
i remember being excited at the thought of this movement kicking off in india. i thought it would be the start of a new era of 0 tolerance. i was to be disappointed it seems. it's disgusting how the first response of the media is to criticise those strong women who were able to come forward and discover the so called "hidden intentions." while there may be crooks in every subject, you should at least be sensitive about the ones who have actually faced trauma. one of the women in my dance class told, "it's disgusting when these old women come forward. if these college girls come forward it's okay." i was appalled to say the least. this is why victims of harassment and even rape never come forward. this poem was written in the point of view of one such woman who was unable to come forward. 
poem and pictures by @xadithix

text:
weak. lost for words. hopeless. 
i kept my secret of sexual abuse from family and friends so i was utterly alone.

the pain seemed constant and never ending. no one knew what i was experiencing and how i felt. no one to comfort me or console me. no one to cry with. no one to pray with.

each day i tried to convince myself that i could get over it. that i was strong enough to handle it. but the truth is, i was a helpless child.

iâ€™d watch my grandmother pray, so i decided at an early age i would pray. although i didnâ€™t have a relationship with the lord, i figured if grandma prayed, maybe prayer would work for me too.

prayer was my only hope.

hope that one day the pain and torment would end. 
i spent years praying a short prayer, â€help meâ€. those two words were all that i could muster up.

now i know, for believers two words are all that is needed in our time of weakness. for we have a great intercessor who can articulate and describe what we feel and need perfectly! â€œin the same way the spirit also helps our weakness; for we do not know how to pray as we should, but the spirit himself intercedes for us with groanings too deep for words;â€ romansâ€¬ â€­8:26â€¬ â€­

text:
after a hiatus, we are eager to finally have our annual haiku year-in-review (hyir) out in the world!~
.
the hyir is a review, reflection, a collaborative timepiece to honor the past year in poetry. ~
.
the editors (miller oberman [ @millerwolf8 ], gabrielle bates [ @gabrielle_bates_ ], elizabeth bradfield [ @e.bradfield ], clayre benzadon [ @clayrebenz ], and alexandra teague [ @alexandra.teague ])
have come together to write about a specific event that stood out to them: ~
.
the us/mexico border wall debate, the shooting at the temple of life in squirrel hill, california wildfires, the 2018 un intergovernmental panel on climate change report, and the ford-kavanaugh hearing (and greater #metoo movement). ~
.
enjoy and please be sure to spread this widely!
.
.
.

text_retweet:
ladies, look at where we are and how far weâ€™ve come. letâ€™s take a minute to collectively be grateful for all of the insane battles women have fought for us. we are grateful for the strength we have galvanized to find our voices on every platform, every corner, and from every direction.

we are still fighting for reproductive rights, and also fighting to maintain ownership of our sexuality every day. this is related to the current shortage of sex ed in the u.s. (only 13 out of 50 states require sex education to be medically accurate). women bear the responsibility to educate themselves and each other because of this shortage in education resources. that responsibility weighs more heavily now than ever, with organizations like planned parenthood under threat. with sexual education comes sexual health, and part of that education is self-exploration. in this post, amara purlle explores how the #metoo movement has changed attitudes or heightened recognition of the freedom to explore our bodies as we see fit.
